            "content": "The Outcome: The homeowner has had zero leaks in the 14 months since repiping (compared to 3 leaks in the previous 7 months). Their water pressure improved significantly throughout the house due to proper pipe sizing and manifold design. They added [link:/services/water-softeners-tucson|water softener installation] ($1,800) to protect fixtures and appliances from hard water, though the PEX pipes themselves don't require softener protection. Total investment: $10,000 (repipe + softener). They recovered $1,350 they would have lost on failed individual repairs. Conservatively estimating they avoided 10 more pinhole leaks over the next 5 years at $400-$800 each, they saved approximately $4,000-$6,000 in future repair costs, plus eliminated the risk of catastrophic pipe failure causing major water damage (potential $10,000-$50,000 loss). Key lesson: When you experience 2+ pinhole leaks within a year in homes with original copper pipes 30+ years old, whole-home repiping is almost always the cost-effective long-term solution."
