            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "However, copper's susceptibility to corrosion in Tucson's extremely hard water (12-16 grains) means repairs may be temporary if the entire system is aging. Copper repairs are NOT recommended when: You've had 2+ pinhole leaks in the past year; Your copper pipes are 25+ years old without water softener protection; You see green corrosion (copper oxidation) on multiple pipes; Your water has reddish-brown discoloration (internal corrosion); Multiple pipe sections show pitting or corrosion when inspected. In these scenarios, the systemic corrosion will continue causing recurring leaks regardless of individual repairs, making repiping more cost-effective long-term."
