            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "When repairing leaks, we often recommend replacing failed copper sections with PEX rather than copper-to-copper repairs. PEX won't corrode like copper regardless of water hardness, costs 20-30% less for materials and labor, installs faster with less disruption, and provides longer-lasting repairs with superior warranty coverage. PEX is the recommended choice for: Any repair in homes with hard water and no water softener; Replacement of failed copper sections showing corrosion; Whole-home repiping projects; Rerouting pipes to avoid problem areas (slab leaks, inaccessible wall cavities); New construction or additions; Any situation where long-term reliability is prioritized. The only situation where copper might be preferred is matching existing exposed copper in visible areas for aesthetic reasons—and even then, PEX can be transitioned to copper at visible points."
